               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols. 1ra-76rb)
 I-1)
                     Introduction (fols. 1ra-10ra) 
 - On John the Evangelist as the author of
                     the book; on the creation and the fall of the angels (fols. 1ra-6ra) 
 -
                     Story of the family of Adam (fols. 6rb-10ra)
 I-2) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus
                     “Miracles of Jesus”: 40 miracles (fols. 10ra-76rb)
 
 Additiones
                     1-4.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Text I-1 has been treated by the scribe as miracles 1-3. Thus, Text
                        I-2) begins with miracle 4 and contains altogether 40 miracles.</note>
                     <note>- Miracles 29 and 30 are arranged in the reverse order.</note>
                     <note>- The Ethiopic number ፮ is identical with ፯ (hand b).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
